President Obama has declared a major disaster in Kentucky due to severe winter storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from March 3-9, 2015. Federal aid will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available to local governments and certain nonprofit organizations for emergency work and repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Snow assistance will also be provided for a continuous 48-hour period in certain counties. Additionally, hazard mitigation measures will be funded for all counties in Kentucky. Joe M. Girot has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations, and further designations may be made based on damage assessments.